Volume management commands:

lsblk   ----> list block devices
file -s /dev/...   ---- > to see which file system is there
fdisk /dev/...   ---> partition
df -h ----> disk free and used with mounted volumes

mount /dev/...  folder

umount folder


use blkid command to get UUID and use UUID instead of /dev/.. in fstab
vim /etc/fstab add entry to make it permanent


ggdsd
